<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,545,713]" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">
This species was described originally from one female and two males from 
<collectingCountry box="[1038,1083,546,569]" name="Iraq" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">Iraq</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bhatti" box="[1101,1241,545,569]" pageId="5" pageNumber="61" refString="Bhatti, J. S. (1988) On the genera Ascirtothrips Priesner and Eremiothrips Priesner (Insecta: Terebrantia: Thripidae). Zoology, 1, 117 - 125." type="journal article" year="1988">
Bhatti 
<number box="[1182,1241,545,569]" pageId="5" pageNumber="61" value="1988.0">1988</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), but was subsequently redescribed by Bhatti (
<number box="[518,580,581,605]" pageId="5" pageNumber="61" value="2009.0">2009</number>
). Moreover, Ramezani 
<emphasis box="[849,901,581,605]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number box="[926,985,581,605]" pageId="5" pageNumber="61" value="2009.0">2009</number>
) recorded large numbers of both sexes from cereal crops in Khuzestan province, south of 
<collectingCountry box="[718,767,618,641]" name="Iran" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">Iran</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
